<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/32017081-victoria"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1401986806i/32017081._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/32017081-victoria">Victoria</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I don&apos;t think I would recommend this book to anyone younger than 15-16. Not that I&apos;m naive enough to think that kids younger than that aren&apos;t exposed <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I don't think I would recommend this book to anyone younger than 15-16. Not that I'm naive enough to think that kids younger than that aren't exposed to sex, drugs, and alcohol in real life, but I simply couldn't in good conscience put this book into the hands of someone younger than that due to the mature themes it contains. Children and teenagers these days are exposed to too much too soon, and I while we can't stop that from happening, we don't have to help it along. Just my two cents. :)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
